ÔÉį	FILE PERMISSIONS

Ôāß	chmod (change mode) is used to change the permissions of a file or directory in Linux.

Ôāß	EX : drwxr-xr‚ÄĒ

o	d   -   directory				
o	r   -    read          -  4
o	w   -    write         -  2
o	x   -    execute       -  1


o	Owner   ÔÉ†   u   ÔÉ†    File owner.
o	Group   ÔÉ†   g   ÔÉ†    Users belonging to the file‚Äôs group.
o	Others  ÔÉ†   o   ÔÉ†    All other users.

Ôāß	chmod u+x file_name
-	u,g,o    ÔÉ†   Users.   
-	+,-      ÔÉ†   Add or Remove permission.
-	r,w,x    ÔÉ†   Permissions.


Ôāß	chmod o-r *
      -	Removes read (r) permission for others (o) from all files in the current directory.

Ôāß	chmod g+r D*
      -	Adds read (r) permission for the group (g) to all files/folders starting with D.

Ôāß	chmod o+x *s
      -	Adds execute (x) permission for others (o) to all files ending with s.		



